20/09/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Boyko Borissov, the former chief secretary of the interior ministry, confirmed on Monday (19 September) that he would run in the 29 October race for mayor of Sofia. Borissov made the announcement immediately after President Georgi Parvanov approved his resignation from the ministry post. 
In other news, another round of flooding hit Bulgaria on Monday, killing one elderly woman and forcing hundreds of evacuate. Six municipalities have again declared an emergency situation. Torrential rains also hit the western part of neighbouring Romania. No injuries were reported there. (bTV, BNR - 20/09/05; bTV, Mediapool, Rompres - 19/09/05)
